  "extra": {
    "note": "FLAGSHIP PIPELINE: one reference image becomes a complete, validated Ideogram 4 prompt with the embedded palette, saved to disk. Flow: LoadImage -> Extractor -> Override (hand-tweak) -> Palette->Global JSON (adds aesthetics/lighting) -> Prompt Assembler (deep-merges the style_description into the base prompt typed in base_json) -> JSON Validator (PASS/FAIL + key-order fix) -> Metadata Embedder (saves the PNG with the prompt in a tEXt chunk). Set the base subject/medium in the Assembler's base_json widget; set aesthetics + lighting on the Palette->Global JSON node. The Validator warns (not errors) about missing top-level keys when the prompt is a partial schema, so it still PASSes. The ShowText node is OPTIONAL (from ComfyUI-Custom-Scripts) and only displays the final JSON -- delete it or swap for any STRING display node if you don't have it. To actually GENERATE, feed the Validator's prompt_json into your Ideogram generation node (API node or a text encoder) instead of / in addition to the Embedder."
